Date: 0/0/1907
Source: NZ Geol. Survey Bulletin
Author:
Vol / Page: No 3. (N.S.) 24
Edition:
Quote: The Wakamarama Range [Nelson] is for the most part densely forested, though there are patches of open <i>pakihi</i> on its summit. [fn] <i>Pakihi </i>(bare) is a Maori term applied to flat, open spaces. <i>Pakihis</i> are generally swampy.
Notes: (Bell)

